1. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper focuses on designing a distributed algorithm for coordinating the parking of autonomous vehicles, which involves multiple agents (AVs) interacting with each other and with the parking facilities. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - Autonomous vehicles are a type of robot, and the paper deals with their coordination and control in a real-world environment. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with designing a system (the coordinated parking problem) and a control algorithm (the distributed algorithm) for achieving a specific objective (supporting V2G services). 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - Although the paper does not explicitly mention machine learning, it is possible that some aspects of the proposed solution methods involve learning or optimization techniques. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper touches upon the societal impact of autonomous vehicles and their potential role in the future transportation system.
